tr.td: For someone without known diabetes, a hemoglobin A1c value
of 6.5% or greater indicates that they may have diabetes
and this should be confirmed with a follow-up test.
For someone with known diabetes, a value <7% indicates
that their diabetes is well controlled and a value greater
than or equal to 7% indicates suboptimal control. A1c
targets should be individualized based on duration of
diabetes, age, co-morbid conditions and other considerations.
Currently, no consensus exists for use of hemoglobin A1c
for diagnosis of diabetes for children.
